-- Kia Motors May Enter India Car Market, Build Plant, Economic Times Reports
-- Victoria Batchelor
-- 2010-06-22T00:40:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/kia-motors-may-enter-india-car-market-build-plant-economic-times-reports.html

          
          
             Kia Motors Corp. is set to enter the
Indian car market and build a manufacturing facility in the 
nation, the Economic Times reported, citing an unnamed person 
with knowledge of the development.  
 Kia will launch compact cars, hatchbacks and entry-level 
sedans initially in India, the newspaper said, citing the 
person, who requested anonymity. An unidentified Kia spokesman 
said the company is conducting a study into possible entry into
India and hasnâ€™t made a decision, the Economic Times reported.  
